result.adr_address: 20 Tat Tung Rd, Tung Chung, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 20 Tat Tung Rd, Tung Chung, Hong Kong
result.name: Urban City Diner

reviews.text: The Urban City Diner’s ambiance is themed around cycling, and offers Western dishes like burgers and pastas. Service was slow and did not check on us because we were seated in the private room, which is a characteristic of bad service. I had the kale salad, which was okay, and the lasagna. The lasagna was obviously frozen, as the center was cold and some of the noodles were still frozen. I had to get the waitress to reheat it. Both the quality of the service and the food were atrocious, and I would not recommend visiting The Urban City Diner.

Food is decent, albeit highly priced. Service is atrocious if you're a foreigner. In a table of two, our food came out 15 minutes apart from each other. We were completely ignored for the better part of the meal, even having to get up to find a waiter and ask for the check after finishing. Meanwhile the couple next to us who were local seemed to have much better service the whole time.

Ordered the lobster pasta and rib eye steak. The lobster is frozen, don’t order it. Very bad quality. The rib eye is okay but definitely not worth the price, a $50 steak at best. The avocado smoothy is pretty nice and they have beer on tap.
Nice ambience..Food taste is okey.. bit expensive.

Nice food and environment, if they can separate the sauce for fish and chips would be even better.

Cheese burger is good but very messy to eat because of the tomato slices inside, probably pan fry them a bit would do the job.

result.adr_address: 20 Tat Tung Rd, Lantau Island, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 20 Tat Tung Rd, Lantau Island, Hong Kong
result.name: Citygate Outlets

reviews.text:
Calling City Gate an Upscale Outlet Mall sounds like an oxymoron. That's exactly what it is.
A nice mall with many shops selling last season products, however bargains though possible are hard to find.
Large areas have closed for refurbishment, good selection of shops however prices are not that cheap like most outlet shopping.
The mall was not bad.  However, the shops were mainly designer brands. And they are targeting mainland China visitors.   It can get pretty crowded in weekends.

Lots of shops...and more shops.
Taste supermarket is great...well stocked with 'international' goodies.
Lots of options for lunch or a quick snack.
You can check out cheap stuff there easily
